Traveling.Companions.and.other.notes: Born in Belfast, Ireland to Robert and Margaret Jane Pinkerton, married Eliza Jane Clokey.  They lived at 40 Linacre Road, Liverpool.

Title: Mr.
Traveling.Companions.and.other.notes: See article, The New York Times, Wednesday, May 26, 1915, page 4, in which he was reported as having said he found two bombs on Deck A just before the ship sailed. The Cunard Line officials ridiculed this idea.

Title: Master
Traveling.Companions.and.other.notes: George was assistant cook in first class. Age 17 (or 16?). George was a friend to Charles Westbury, second cook,q.v. Lived on Oakes Street in Liverpool. Retired to a sailors home in the 1970s. Mentioned in Hickey/Smith on pages 52+, 101, 171, 195, 206, 230, 314.

Title: Mr.
Traveling.Companions.and.other.notes: Joseph was Georges father. Suffered from bronchitis. Went down with the ship. Mentioned in Hickey/Smith on pages 53, 171, 206 and 230.
